# Copy to .env and fill in. Used by server/index.js (Spotify, Claude, Luffa, YouTube).
# Start API: cd server && node index.js (default PORT=4000). From repo root, npm run dev (or npm run preview)
# proxies /api to http://127.0.0.1:4000 so Crystal + globe API calls work without VITE_API_URL.
# Luffa uses polling: set LUFFA_BOT_SECRET (Robot Key from Luffa dashboard).
# Crystal Ball: set YOUTUBE_API_KEY for in-browser music (Google Cloud Console, enable YouTube Data API v3).
# Spotify (globe + Crystal matching + playlists): SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID, SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET, SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN
# Crystal: max ms per video for Spotify search before skipping (default 22000). Skipped rows are not added to playlists.
# CRYSTAL_SPOTIFY_LOOKUP_MS=22000
# Crystal “Archive session” saves JSON to ../archive/ (gitignored *.json).

LUFFA_BOT_SECRET=
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=
